 The file which contains the IP address of the DBS server we're using is [resolv.conf].
 It can be found at [/etc]. It we check it like [cat /etc/resolv.conf] we'll obtain something like:

#
# Mac OS X Notice
#
# This file is not used by the host name and address resolution
# or the DNS query routing mechanisms used by most processes on
# this Mac OS X system.
#
# This file is automatically generated.
#
domain 42.fr
nameserver 10.51.1.42
nameserver 10.51.1.43
